They are all true as well, I've checked the facts. This is a Foreign Stout from their BA-series released in December 2017, and I found it in the stash when I was on my way to piano lesson and grabbed it on the go. Aroma carries bourbon notes for sure. Maybe the slightly lower ABV gives clearance for the bourbon to come forward? Roasted malts and dried fruit as well. Taste is roasted notes with licorice and medium sweet chocolates. Rich taste for the abv. Light ashy as well. Medium bitter and the bourbon notes are interweaved into the roasted notes and balanced very well. Interesting take on making it a stout in the "Foreign" style, I found that it let all the taste notes to come forward in another way than usual. 4.0/5.0 #amager #amagerbryghus #paulthepackingpianoplayer #danishcraftbeer #foreignstout #boxbeers #boxbeerscom #drinkitlikeyoumeanit #thebeernation #hopmaestroEr egentlig pÃ¦nt priviligeret med, at jeg mere eller mindre bor tÃ¦t pÃ¥ natur og vand i flere former, nÃ¦rmest uanset om jeg gÃ¥r den ene eller anden vej, nÃ¥r jeg forlader matriklen (og sÃ¥ i Ã¸vrigt med indre by 10 min vÃ¦k pÃ¥ cykel)... sÃ¥ herfra skal lyde:
